8 cups buttermilk 
2 tablespoons sour cream
 1 jar shredded marinated beets (This is the easy way. If you prefer, you can peel and boil your own fresh beets (about 2-3 large beets), and add salt, pepper, sugar and vinegar to taste.)
2 cucumbers, shredded
 3 tablespoons chopped dill 
3 tablespoons chopped scallions
 2 hard-boiled eggs, chopped 
boiled potatoes (optional)

In a large bowl, whisk together buttermilk and sour cream.
Add beets, cucumber, scallions, eggs, and dill; mix.
Serve saltibarsciai chilled with a dollop of sour cream and a side of warm potatoes.
